Another general strike took place in March 1919. Translation by Google from <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berliner_M%c3%a4rzk%c3%a4mpfe" rel="nofollow">de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berliner_M%C3%A4rzk%C3%A4mpfe</a>: &quot;The Berlin March bouts of 1919 demanded more than 1,200 deaths and are thus one of the most bloody conflicts in the context of the revolutionary clashes in Germany after the end of the First World War. They can be dated from 3 March to 16 March 1919. Parallel to the March battles, general strikes also took place in the Ruhr area and in the central German industrial district around Halle / Merseburg. ...
Already at the outbreak of the general strike on 3 March there were riots and looting in the inner city and raids on police officers in the vicinity of Alexanderplatz. ... On March 4, the invasion of units of the General Command commenced into the city. On Alexanderplatz there were serious clashes with the Volksmarinedivision, after their units had been bombarded by soldiers of the German Schutzdivision.&quot;

