There is this note about Jose Grau from the Emma Goldman Papers editor:
&quot;aliases Arnoldo Sapelano and Arnold Sopelno. Spanish Anarchist and IWW member. Grau was an organizer of the Spanish branch of the IWW and entered the country in June 1917 from Progresso, Mexico aboard a Norwegian steamship, the Wyking. In May 1918 Grau attended an IWW convention in Philadelphia held by the Marine Transport Workers. On 23 February 1919 Grau was arrested along with thirteen other Spanish anarchists as part of an alleged attempt by Grupo pro Prensa (literally, &quot;Group for the Press&quot;; Press Advocacy Group) to assassinate President Wilson. Grau and his comrades were soon released with the help of Harry Weinberger, but Grau was subsequently scheduled for deportation. Recht defended him at his hearing. &quot;
<a href="http://editorsnotes.org/projects/emma/topics/183/" rel="nofollow">editorsnotes.org/projects/emma/topics/183/</a>

