&quot;Captain Richards was of an English family of this name that came originally from France. On his mother's side he was a grandson of Captain H. H. Cocke, U. S. Navy, and Captain in the Confederate Navy; on his father's side he was a grandson of Major James Russell Richards, of Virginia. He was descended (on both sides) from twenty-two heroes who at different times bore arms in the defense of their Country. 

Captain Richards married Ada Nicoll Knight, only daughter of Right Rev. Albion W. Knight, Vice-Chancellor of the University of the South. He left one daughter, Elise Knight Richards. &quot;

